# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Build-context whitelist for the feishu-claude-agent image.
#
# The Dockerfile (docker/Dockerfile, passed via `dockerfile:` / `-f`) only ever
# COPYs two files — agent_runner.py and agent_runner_opencode.py. Everything else
# in the repo is irrelevant to the image, so we EXCLUDE IT ALL by default and
# allow only those two files through.
#
# Why a whitelist (not a blacklist): this guarantees that secrets, logs,
# sessions.json, bridge.pid, .env, .git, .venv, *.bak, scripts/, and any file
# accidentally committed in the FUTURE can never reach the Docker daemon or
# end up in an image layer — even though the Dockerfile itself wouldn't COPY
# them. Defense in depth.
#
# NOTE: `**` matches everything recursively. The Dockerfile is read via its `-f`
# path and is NOT subject to .dockerignore, so docker/ does not need to be
# allowed here.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Exclude everything by default.
**

# Allow exactly the two files the Dockerfile COPYs into the image.
!agent_runner.py
!agent_runner_opencode.py
